paragraphs.title: Get the files from S3 and move them to HDFS for use with Spark
paragraphs.text:
%sh

echo "getting data from block store"
tmp_dir=/tmp/zeppelin/chi_data_cleaning
crime_dir=$tmp_dir/data/crime
mkdir -p $crime_dir
cd $crime_dir
aws s3 sync s3://carolyndubywestodsc2017/data/crime $crime_dir

echo "unzip files so they can be loaded into data frames"
for f in *.zip; do
   unzip -o $f
done

echo "put the files in hdfs"
hdfs dfs -rm -r -skipTrash /user/zeppelin/odsc/chi
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /user/zeppelin/odsc/chi
hdfs dfs -moveFromLocal /tmp/zeppelin/chi_data_cleaning/data /user/zeppelin/odsc/chi

paragraphs.title: Read the CSV files, Schema inference returns mostly strings
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.spark

// read CSV files into a DataFrame
val chi_crime_df_raw = spark.read.option("header", "true").option("timestampFormat", "dd/MM/yyyy hh:mm:ss a").option("inferSchema", "true").csv("/user/zeppelin/odsc/chi/data/crime/*.csv")

// make it easier to use data frame by removing spaces from column names
val stripped_column_names = chi_crime_df_raw.columns.map(orig_column_name => if (orig_column_name == "_c0") "unnamed" else orig_column_name.replaceAll("\\s", ""))
val chi_crime_df_headers_corrected = chi_crime_df_raw.toDF(stripped_column_names : _*)
chi_crime_df_headers_corrected.printSchema()

paragraphs.title: Remove duplicate header lines and duplicate cases
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.spark

// remove records with invalid years
val years = chi_crime_df_headers_corrected.select($"Year").distinct
years.show

// track number of records before removing records with bad years
val original_record_count = chi_crime_df_raw.count

val chi_crime_df_clean_header = chi_crime_df_headers_corrected.filter($"Year" rlike "^\\d{4}")
val after_year_cleaning_record_count = chi_crime_df_clean_header.count
val records_removed = original_record_count - after_year_cleaning_record_count

val duplicate_cases = chi_crime_df_headers_corrected.groupBy("CaseNumber").count().filter($"count" > 1)
val duplicate_case_count = duplicate_cases.count
duplicate_cases.show

val chi_crime_distinct = chi_crime_df_clean_header.distinct
val distict_removed_records = after_year_cleaning_record_count - chi_crime_distinct.count

paragraphs.title: Convert types on clean data set
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.spark
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._;
val chi_crime_converted = chi_crime_distinct.select( 
    $"CaseNumber".as("caseNumber"), 
    unix_timestamp($"Date", "MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss a").cast(TimestampType).as("reportDateTime"), 
    $"Block".as("block"),
    $"PrimaryType".as("primaryType"),
    $"Description".as("description"),
    $"LocationDescription".as("locationDescription"),
    $"Arrest".cast(BooleanType).as("arrest"),
    $"Domestic".cast(BooleanType).as("domestic"),
    $"Beat".cast(IntegerType).as("beat"),
    $"District".cast(IntegerType).as("district"),
    $"Ward".cast(IntegerType).as("ward"),
    $"CommunityArea".cast(IntegerType).as("communityArea"),
    $"FBICode".as("fbiCode"),
    $"Year".as("year"),
    $"Latitude".as("latitude"),
    $"Longitude".as("longitude"),
    $"Location".as("location")
    )
    .withColumn("weekOfYear", date_format($"reportDateTime", "w"))
    .withColumn("dayOfWeek", date_format($"reportDateTime", "EEEE"))
    .withColumn("hourOfDay", date_format($"reportDateTime", "H"))

chi_crime_converted.show
